## MCP Tool to Cursor Rule Mapping

| MCP Tool                  | Enforced Cursor Rule(s)                                 |
|--------------------------|--------------------------------------------------------|
| enforce_etl_guidelines    | ETL Process Guidelines (`etl_rules.mdc`)               |
| check_pandas_nulls        | Pandas Null Handling Guidelines (`pandas_null_handling.mdc`) |
| enforce_pandas_types      | Pandas DataFrame Type Enforcement (`pandas_dataframe_type_enforcement.mdc`) |
| validate_tvtms_counts     | TVTMS Expected Count Validation (`tvtms_expected_count.mdc`) |
| check_tvtms_format        | TVTMS Text File Format Guidelines (`tvtms_txt_only.mdc`) |
| log_action                | Logging and Error Handling (`logging_and_error_handling.mdc`) |
| check_ports, normalize_reference | Server Management, Data Normalization (see docs) |
| validate_json_schema      | DSPy/JSON Schema Integration (see docs)                |
| suggest_incremental_change | Rule Creation Guide (`rule_creation_guide.mdc`)                                 |

## Enforcement
- All MCP tools must reference the relevant Cursor rule in their docstring or help output.
- Documentation and onboarding must point to this mapping for clarity.
- All new rules or tools should be added to this mapping for discoverability.
